***
***	<comment from="devstral-small-2">
***	The original code defines a function `f` that computes X raised to the power of N (i.e., X^N) using recursion. The base case is `f(X, 0) = 1`, and the recursive case is `f(X, s N) = X * f(X, N)`. This is a standard recursive definition for exponentiation.
***	</comment>
***

fmod MAIN is
	protecting INT .

	op f : Nat Nat -> Nat .

	vars X N : Nat .

	eq f(X, 0) = 1 .
	eq f(X, s N) = X * f(X, N) .
endfm